        public Vtree(long[] varOrder,
             VtreeType type)
        Creates a vtree of the given type whose left-to-right variable ordering is given in array varOrder. The contents of array varOrder must be a permutation of the integers from 1 to varOrder.length.
        Parameters:
        varOrder -
        type -

      • Vtree

        public Vtree(int varCount,
             long[] xConstrained,
             VtreeType type)
        Creates an X-constrained vtree over a given number of variables (var count). The input is X var is an array of size var count + 1 specifying variables X. For variables i where 1 ≤ i ≤ var count, if is X var[i] is 1 then i ∈ X, and if it is 0 then i 6∈ X. The type of a vtree may be "right" (right linear), "left" (left linear), "vertical", "balanced", or "random". Creates a vtree of the given type whose left-to-right variable ordering is given in array varOrder. The contents of array varOrder must be a permutation of the integers from 1 to varOrder.length.
        Parameters:
        varCount -
        xConstrained -
        type -
